Introduction

8TURN, formerly known as BOM (Boys Of MNH), is an eight-member boy group under MNH Entertainment.
They made their official debut on January 30th, 2023 with the mini album "8TURNRISE."

Their name means 'the turn of eight boys with infinite potential', and contains the ambition to lead a new generation in the K-pop scene, referencing the group's eight members.

On March 6th, 2024, 8TURN made their Japanese debut with the digital single "Ru-Pum-Pum Japanese ver."

8TURN participated in "Road to Kingdom: Ace of Ace."
